Let’s be honest – who here doesn’t love sushi? I could eat it daily although I don’t need or want that much rice every week. Which is why this low-carb, 100% plant-based rainbow cucumber sushi is the perfect compromise! I’ve shared options similar in my story for years but this is awesome! By @alphafoodie

This rainbow cucumber sushi is not only 100% plant-based , but can be made in under 15 minutes and perfect for a healthy, delicious low-carb lunch or snack served alongside a delicious vegan avocado dip!

FIVE Super Healthy Vegan Lunch Recipes! 🌱🍱🌱 *Swipe for videos and see below for calories and details!
Which is your favourite 1-5?!🙊🤩
⠀
🙌
So Delicious and Quick Vegan lunches for the new week!…By @fivesechealth
🙌
⠀
⠀
1 🥪 EXTRA PROTEIN GUAC TOASTIE
⠀⠀ ⠀ 350 CALORIES
Tofu adds extra protein and a really nice texture!👌🏼
HOW: Mash 1/2 avocado, 1/4 cup crumbled firm tofu, basil, lemon juice, s+p, 1/4 tsp garlic powder. Spread on wholewheat or your favourite bread and grill until golden.
⠀
⠀
2 🌯 CRUNCHY HUMMUS WRAP
⠀⠀ ⠀ 400 CALORIES
Really perfect on the go! Just wrap in paper!
INGREDIENTS: Chopped cucumber, whole wheat tortilla, tomato, red onion, parsley, hummus, lettuce, cooked quinoa, red cabbage.
⠀
⠀
3 🌮 SIMPLY VEGAN TACOS
⠀⠀ ⠀ 300 CALORIES
Simple yet flavourful. Who else loooove tacos?
HOW: Mash avocado with pepper and 1 tbsp lime.
Then cook 230g black beans with water, 1 tbsp cumin and 1 tsp smoked paprika. Serve in wheat tortillas with avo, coriander, corn, chili & coriander
⠀
⠀
4 🍝 CREAMY VEGAN PASTA
⠀⠀ ⠀ 350 CALORIES
Creamy smoked paprika pasta 🤤
HOW: Boil Pasta. Sauce: Boil cashews then until smooth and creamy blend with 1 cup water, lemon juice, 2 tbsp nutritional yeast, basil, 2 tsp smoked paprika powder, s+p. Sauté 2 onions, cherry tomatoes and spinach, then add in the sauce and pasta. Serve!
⠀
⠀
5 🥗 VEGAN POKE BOWL
⠀⠀ ⠀ 300 CALORIES
The nori sheet gives a fishy flavour without the fish!🐟
HOW: Sauce: 4 tbsp coconut milk, 2 tsp maple syrup, 1/2 tbsp lime juice and 1 tsp sambal olek. Coriander, cucumber, avocado, nori sheet, red cabbage, rice and tofu in a pan with some tamari or soy sauce add with the sauce.

SUPER MOIST Strawberry 🍓🍌🍞 Banana Bread | VEGAN + GF
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This is one of my favorite recipes Vegan & GF STRAWBERRY BANANA BREAD! Or should I say.. CAKE 🍰 It’s SO DELICIOUS !!…By @peanutbutterandjillybeans
 
I couldn’t stop eating it! You’ll be amazed at how simple it is to bake, the small amount of ingredients you need, and how perfect it comes out. The texture was so dense, moist, and oh so fluffy at the same time! You’re 1 bowl & 40 minutes away from berry banana heaven!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
Vegan Strawberry Banana Bread 🍞🍓🍌
📝 Ingredients 3 mashed ripe bananas 2 flax eggs (2 tbsp flax seed meal mixed with 4 tbsp warm water) 1/2 cup melted coconut oil 1/2 cup maple syrup 1/2 cup almond milk 2 cups of gluten free or oat flour 1 tsp baking soda + 1 tsp baking powder 1/2 tsp salt 1 tsp vanilla 1 cup sliced strawberries ⠀⠀ 
 ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

Raise your hand if you like A LOT of FLAVOR in your meals?! If your hand is up, then this recipe is for YOU!…By @cleanfoodcrush 

While these bowls are not spicy-hot, they are packed full of delicious spices that add loads of flavor! 

I made these Spiced Chicken Bowls for dinner and all of our teenagers cleaned up their bowls and everything left in the pans. 🏆WINNER 

These bowls would work fabulously to bring to work or school for lunch because they are great eaten cold. #MealPrep 

Be sure to use brown BASMATI rice for this recipe because different types of brown rice cook up differently. Brown basmati takes less time to cook than regular short-grain brown rice.

🍜 Turmeric has been a popular spice in Indian and Asian food for centuries, but it has become a global favorite over the past few years.

💛Turmeric gets its health benefits from its main active ingredient, curcumin, which is LOADED with antioxidants and is believed to have anti-inflammatory properties. (and it’s even great for some pets, also! - But check with your vet of course!) 

🧡Researchers believe that chronic inflammation plays a significant role in all sorts of chronic diseases, from heart disease to cancer. 

✅ Plus, curcumin is believed to boost your brain function, ease arthritis pain, and even help with depression. 

🍵Turmeric adds a rich flavor to recipes and even has found its way into yummy turmeric lattes! Add it to rice, chilis, stews, and stir-fries for a unique flavor. 

⁉️Have you had any turmeric lately!?

Want to get the most juice possible from each of your fresh lemons or limes? Of course, we do! Here's a quick trick: 

On your counter or a cutting board, press and roll your lemon/lime back and forth very firmly with your hands.

BAKED OATMEAL CUPS 🍓

If you’re not a morning person/busyyyyy - I think you might love these oatmeal cups!…By @projectsunny

Make a batch of these and you’ve got a “grab-n-go” breakfast/snack for the next couple of days 💅🏼

You can mix up the flavors with different fruits, chocolate chips, and nuts. See the notes at the bottom of the recipe for some tips 💕

RECIPE👇

Servings: 12 oatmeal cups

Ingredients:
• 2-1/2 cups rolled oats
• 1/4 cup coconut sugar, optional (see notes)
• 1 teaspoon baking powder
• 1 teaspoon cinnamon
• 1/4 teaspoon salt 
• 4 bananas, mashed
• 1/2 cup milk of choice
• 2 flax seed eggs (see notes)
• 1 teaspoon vanilla extract

Directions:
1) Preheat oven to 350°F. Line a 12-slot muffin tin with cupcake liners. Set aside.
2) In a mixing bowl, combine all of the dry ingredients and mix well (oats, sugar, baking powder, cinnamon, salt).
3) In a separate mixing bowl, combine the remaining wet ingredients. Whisk together until very well combined.
4) Combine the wet and dry ingredients and use a spatula to mix them together.
5) Evenly distribute the oatmeal mixture into the cupcake liners. Top with any fruits, chocolate, etc that you might want to use.
6) Bake for ~30 minutes, or until a toothpick stuck in the center comes out clean. Cool for a few minutes before diving in!

NOTES:
1) SUGAR. Personally I do not always use the sugar in this recipe. I like it better without. If you want to leave the sugar out, remember you could always use a bit of agave/honey drizzle on top if you get a sweet tooth 💕

2) EGGS. For a flax seed egg, mix 1 tablespoon ground flax seed with 3 tablespoons water, place in the fridge for 15 minutes before using (this recipe calls for 2 eggs, so double that recipe).

3) STORAGE. Store in the fridge for up to 5 days.

ENJOY ❤️

😋 BAKED OATS (in loaf form)

this FLOUR-LESS VEGAN BREAD was a hit long before the baked oats trend😉 and it requires no eggs, no protein powder, no beans, and I can almost guarantee you have all 6 ingredients just sitting in your pantry, waiting to be baked! I'm not vegan, but I can sure eat like one 🙊
 
DRY:
1 cup oats
3/4 cup pure cacao powder
1 tsp baking soda 
 
WET:
1 1/2 cup apple sauce
1/3 cup drippy almond butter
1/2 cup nut milk
Pulse dry ingredients in a blender until it forms a fine powder. 
 
Add wet ingredients and blend again to form a thick batter. 
 
Bake in a pan at 350 F for 30-40 minutes.
